{
  "doc_id": "59223",
  "text": "In the theory of stochastic Volterra equations we are interested not only in the existance, uniqueness and regularity of solutions but in some asymptotics, too. The paper [CITATION_1] is concerned with a limit measure of stochastic Volterra equation driven by very general noise in a form of a spatially homogeneous Wiener process, with values in the space of tempered distributions S ′ (R d ). That paper provides necessary and sufficient conditions for the existence of the limit measure and additionally, it gives a form of any limit measure.",
